<paragraph blockId="17.[151,684,168,501]" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">
This is a rare species that has only been collected twice in the NW of the island. Following the notes of 
<collectionCode box="[327,427,229,255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">PERRIER</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[443,474,234,253]" country="Hungary" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15158" name="Debrecen University" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">DE</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[490,517,234,253]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15420" name="University of California" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">LA</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[533,550,229,255]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[552,623,234,254]" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">ÂTHIE</collectionCode>
and HUMBERT, the stems are reddish, the leaves are dull green above with a paler median nerve and the under side is red. The lateral sepals are mauve or rose-coloured and the petals are rose-flushed or mauve on the back, paler on the inner surface. The hood is green on the back with three keels in relief, within on the inner face are a series of olive or brownish radiating lines.
</paragraph>
